<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended straight in front of you, palms down.</li>



<li>Tighten your abdominal muscles to stabilize your spine.</li>



<li>Simultaneously, push through your hands to raise your arms, chest, and legs off the ground, keeping them straight.</li>



<li>Maintain the elevated position for a few seconds, feeling the contraction in your lower back.</li>



<li>Slowly return to the starting position with control.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your neck neutral by looking down at the floor to avoid strain.</li>



<li>Move smoothly and avoid jerky motions to maintain control.</li>



<li>Start with shorter holds and gradually increase the duration as your strength improves.</li>



<li>Ensure your movements are synchronized between your upper and lower body.</li>
